WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.111 --> 00:00:12.547
(groans)

2
00:00:12.647 --> 00:00:14.682
Does he not think
there could be ghosts in here.

3
00:00:14.782 --> 00:00:16.283
or does he just not care?

4
00:00:16.383 --> 00:00:19.954
Clippings not even landing
in basket. Is disgusting.

5
00:00:20.053 --> 00:00:21.623
And that's coming from a man
who just told a story

6
00:00:21.723 --> 00:00:24.291
about ripping out
a Dane's entrails.

7
00:00:24.391 --> 00:00:25.593
This is
a bathroom activity. man.

8
00:00:25.693 --> 00:00:27.227
You don't do this
in the main area.

9
00:00:27.327 --> 00:00:29.296
HETTY:
What? Now. don't cut
the pinky one.

10
00:00:29.396 --> 00:00:31.098
That's nature's cocaine spoon.

11
00:00:31.198 --> 00:00:32.266
Hmm.

12
00:00:32.366 --> 00:00:33.968
At least it over now.

13
00:00:34.067 --> 00:00:35.803
Oh.

14
00:00:35.904 --> 00:00:38.773
Oh. and he's going
for the foot. Buckle up.

15
00:00:38.873 --> 00:00:41.643
Sass. there's someone out here
who's looking for you.

16
00:00:41.743 --> 00:00:44.378
Sorry. kid. that smoke break

17
00:00:44.478 --> 00:00:46.581
took a lot longer
than I expected.

18
00:00:46.681 --> 00:00:48.616
Joan. Oh. my God.

19
00:00:48.716 --> 00:00:50.450
Uh... wh-where were you?

20
00:00:50.552 --> 00:00:52.419
-Where-where have you been?
-It's a long story.

21
00:00:52.520 --> 00:00:54.388
I'll tell you all about it.
but in the meantime.

22
00:00:54.488 --> 00:00:56.256
you just gonna
stand there gawking.

23
00:00:56.356 --> 00:00:58.191
or you gonna lay one on me?

24
00:00:59.192 --> 00:01:00.294
Kiss her. you fool!

25
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:01.495
(Alberta giggles)

26
00:01:05.432 --> 00:01:08.002
Aw. this is just
like in the movies.

27
00:01:08.101 --> 00:01:11.438
Ooh. we got a big boy.
Timber!

28
00:01:11.539 --> 00:01:13.608
Oh. What was that?

29
00:01:13.708 --> 00:01:17.110
Just Jay's toenail
flying through your head.

30
00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:19.881
Oh. That one got some air.

31
00:01:20.882 --> 00:01:22.316
Welcome back. Joan.

32
00:01:22.449 --> 00:01:24.519
♪ ♪

33
00:01:27.454 --> 00:01:29.524
TREVOR:
Well. it's a done deal.

34
00:01:29.624 --> 00:01:31.793
Mayor Tad is now
the majority stakeholder

35
00:01:31.893 --> 00:01:34.127
in Woodstone.

36
00:01:34.227 --> 00:01:35.863
So. are they technically
a throuple now?

37
00:01:35.964 --> 00:01:38.633
I mean.
in the business sense. sure.

38
00:01:38.733 --> 00:01:40.668
What about in the "doing it
together in a waterbed" sense?

39
00:01:40.768 --> 00:01:43.871
Not yet. but once you let
a silver fox into the henhouse.

40
00:01:43.972 --> 00:01:45.039
all bets are off.

41
00:01:45.138 --> 00:01:46.708
So. what are these pictures for?

42
00:01:46.808 --> 00:01:48.810
Oh. just a little press release

43
00:01:48.910 --> 00:01:50.812
announcing my investment
in Woodstone

44
00:01:50.912 --> 00:01:53.246
and how I. Mayor Tad.
swept in and rescued

45
00:01:53.347 --> 00:01:55.482
a local business
from financial ruin.

46
00:01:55.583 --> 00:01:58.151
I was a huge supporter
of local businesses in my day.

47
00:01:58.251 --> 00:02:00.054
That's why I frequented Scores

48
00:02:00.153 --> 00:02:02.690
instead of one of the
big chain strip clubs.

49
00:02:02.790 --> 00:02:05.059
So. uh. Tad. in terms of this

50
00:02:05.158 --> 00:02:07.895
new partnership.
how exactly does it work?

51
00:02:07.996 --> 00:02:09.897
You just get on the waterbed.
put on some CCR.

52
00:02:09.998 --> 00:02:11.866
and don't overthink it.
(clicks tongue)

53
00:02:11.966 --> 00:02:14.068
Yeah. like. I'm planning on
revamping the new spring menu.

54
00:02:14.167 --> 00:02:15.737
Is that something
you want to be looped in on?

55
00:02:15.837 --> 00:02:17.839
Let me stop you right there.
I want you

56
00:02:17.939 --> 00:02:20.173
to keep doing what you're doing.
I believe in you two.

57
00:02:20.273 --> 00:02:23.845
Oh. that's nice.
Stupid but nice.

58
00:02:23.945 --> 00:02:26.146
Plus. I'm far too busy
to weigh in

59
00:02:26.246 --> 00:02:27.882
on day-to-day issues
here at Woodstone.

60
00:02:27.982 --> 00:02:29.851
SAMANTHA:
Oh. I'm sure.

61
00:02:29.951 --> 00:02:31.786
Being a mayor must be
a very big and important job.

62
00:02:31.886 --> 00:02:36.758
Exactly. Well. I'm off to
a ribbon cutting at a dog spa.

63
00:02:36.858 --> 00:02:40.762
Okay. Tad. Uh. we'll hold down
the fort here.

64
00:02:40.862 --> 00:02:43.330
(laughs) Everybody thinks
they can hold down a fort.

65
00:02:43.430 --> 00:02:45.432
Trust me. it's not as easy
as it sounds.

66
00:02:45.533 --> 00:02:47.769
There's flags to raise.
There's cannons to polish.

67
00:02:47.869 --> 00:02:49.537
There's horsemeat to ration.
(laughs)

68
00:02:49.637 --> 00:02:51.873
It's-it's a whole.
it's a whole production.

69
00:02:51.973 --> 00:02:53.340
<i>JOAN:</i>
<i>So.</i>

70
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:55.275
there I was. on a flight
back to the States.

71
00:02:55.375 --> 00:02:58.412
Suddenly. turbulence threw me
from my seat.

72
00:02:58.513 --> 00:03:00.114
I flew straight out
of the plane.

73
00:03:00.213 --> 00:03:02.016
That's why I always sit
in the center aisle.

74
00:03:02.116 --> 00:03:03.618
Lots of walk-throughs.
but better than

75
00:03:03.718 --> 00:03:05.285
falling out over
the Atlantic. (laughs)

76
00:03:05.385 --> 00:03:07.622
You fell out of an airplane?

77
00:03:07.722 --> 00:03:09.090
Landed smack-dab in the middle

78
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:11.458
of what I later learned
was Mongolia.

79
00:03:11.559 --> 00:03:15.262
Lot of yaks. Not a lot of direct
flights back to LaGuardia.

80
00:03:15.362 --> 00:03:16.597
So how did you get back?

81
00:03:16.698 --> 00:03:18.099
I hoofed it.

82
00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:19.967
Through the desert.
over mountain ranges.

83
00:03:20.068 --> 00:03:21.969
I thought of giving up
many times.

84
00:03:22.070 --> 00:03:24.772
but one thing kept me going--

85
00:03:24.872 --> 00:03:27.307
the thought of making it
back to you. Sass.

86
00:03:27.407 --> 00:03:29.977
-Aw.
-That is so sweet.

87
00:03:30.078 --> 00:03:32.146
Yeah. Speaking of sweet stories.

88
00:03:32.245 --> 00:03:34.314
do you remember the holiday
rom-com that we discussed

89
00:03:34.414 --> 00:03:37.652
last time you were here?
<i>Polar Opposites?</i>

90
00:03:37.752 --> 00:03:40.387
Yes. of course.
It was set at the north pole.

91
00:03:40.487 --> 00:03:42.657
it had two characters
who were very different.

92
00:03:42.757 --> 00:03:45.325
and one of them
was named Jenny Polar.

93
00:03:45.425 --> 00:03:46.828
(chuckles)
Exactly.

94
00:03:46.928 --> 00:03:48.495
Well. I actually banged out
a first draft

95
00:03:48.596 --> 00:03:49.997
and I printed it out for you.

96
00:03:50.098 --> 00:03:51.666
so if you had a minute.

97
00:03:51.766 --> 00:03:54.602
I would love to get
a real screenwriter's opinion.

98
00:03:54.702 --> 00:03:57.337
Oh. well. can't turn the pages.

99
00:03:57.437 --> 00:03:58.639
Which is why
I laid it out for you

100
00:03:58.740 --> 00:03:59.907
on the floor
of the upstairs den.

101
00:04:00.007 --> 00:04:01.341
This woman is relentless.

102
00:04:01.441 --> 00:04:04.178
-It would be my pleasure.
-Great. (chuckles)

103
00:04:04.277 --> 00:04:06.080
I'll rescue you soon.

104
00:04:07.081 --> 00:04:08.783
Oh. this is a disaster.

105
00:04:08.883 --> 00:04:10.685
Oh. I don't know.
I read an earlier floor draft.

106
00:04:10.785 --> 00:04:13.320
-I think it had some fun stuff.
-I'm talking about Joan.

107
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:15.355
She doesn't know that
I hooked up with Bela.

108
00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:17.191
Well. in-in your defense.
Joan didn't come back

109
00:04:17.290 --> 00:04:18.693
when she said she was going to.

110
00:04:18.793 --> 00:04:21.129
It's "lost at sea" rules.
Someone disappears.

111
00:04:21.229 --> 00:04:23.631
at-at a certain point.
it's only human to move on.

112
00:04:23.731 --> 00:04:25.867
It's like that movie
we watched. <i>Cast Away.</i>

113
00:04:25.967 --> 00:04:27.300
Tom Hanks was stuck
on the island.

114
00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:29.003
Helen Hunt moved on.
She didn't know.

115
00:04:29.103 --> 00:04:31.304
A-And Tom Hanks cheated on her
with that volleyball.

116
00:04:31.404 --> 00:04:33.141
-What?
-No. he didn't.

117
00:04:33.241 --> 00:04:35.442
Well. they didn't show it.
but something happened.

118
00:04:35.543 --> 00:04:38.345
You don't scream like that
when a "friend" goes away.

119
00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:40.782
I need to tell Joan about Bela.

120
00:04:40.882 --> 00:04:42.784
No. You didn't do
anything wrong.

121
00:04:42.884 --> 00:04:44.218
If you tell her.
it's just gonna hurt her.

122
00:04:44.351 --> 00:04:47.021
That's true.
I guess you're right.

123
00:04:47.121 --> 00:04:51.391
"Wilson! Wilson! I loved
being with you romantically!"

124
00:04:51.491 --> 00:04:53.060
Is the subtext. Right?

125
00:04:53.161 --> 00:04:54.929
I can't believe
you guys didn't get that.

126
00:04:56.164 --> 00:04:58.566
-Hey. Sam.
-Hey. Mark.

127
00:04:58.666 --> 00:05:01.169
So. are they in here?
The ghosts?

128
00:05:01.269 --> 00:05:03.004
Yeah. uh. there's a Viking.

129
00:05:03.104 --> 00:05:05.405
a finance bro. a scout leader.
and a hippie.

130
00:05:05.506 --> 00:05:07.909
And a purple astronaut
named Ronald.

131
00:05:08.009 --> 00:05:09.644
Only you can see him. Flower.

132
00:05:09.744 --> 00:05:11.712
Right. 'cause of the drugs.

133
00:05:11.813 --> 00:05:13.915
I'm not gonna lie.
I'm freaking out. Sam.

134
00:05:14.015 --> 00:05:15.850
I-I wish you'd never
told me about them.

135
00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:17.218
You know. I've been driving home

136
00:05:17.350 --> 00:05:19.020
every time I need
to go to the bathroom?

137
00:05:19.120 --> 00:05:21.321
Oh. you don't need to do that.
They're pretty respectful.

138
00:05:21.421 --> 00:05:23.591
Besides. you probably have
ghosts at your place. too.

139
00:05:23.691 --> 00:05:25.593
-What?
-How that helpful. Sam?

140
00:05:25.693 --> 00:05:28.095
I've been to Mark's place.
There's a lady with no face.

141
00:05:28.196 --> 00:05:31.098
Chimp attack. But maybe
that's a "just for us" story.

142
00:05:31.199 --> 00:05:32.934
-Hey. babe.
-(screams)

143
00:05:33.034 --> 00:05:34.569
We got to turn on
the local news right now.

144
00:05:34.669 --> 00:05:36.204
Okay. what's going on?

145
00:05:36.304 --> 00:05:39.073
The mayor's in hot water.
that's what's going on.

146
00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:40.775
<i>NEWSCASTER (over TV):</i>
<i>Allegations are swirling.</i>

147
00:05:40.875 --> 00:05:43.410
<i>the mayor used</i>
<i>city workers to repair</i>

148
00:05:43.511 --> 00:05:46.446
<i>a broken driveway gate</i>
<i>at his private residence.</i>

149
00:05:46.547 --> 00:05:48.415
<i>They're calling it "Gate-gate."</i>

150
00:05:48.516 --> 00:05:50.383
Huh. that's sort of clever.

151
00:05:50.483 --> 00:05:53.254
<i>I caught up with the mayor</i>
<i>inside City Hall moments ago.</i>

152
00:05:53.353 --> 00:05:55.623
<i>The allegations are false.</i>
<i>I look forward to rigorously</i>

153
00:05:55.723 --> 00:05:57.792
<i>defending myself at the next</i>
<i>City Council meeting.</i>

154
00:05:57.892 --> 00:05:59.961
<i>What about security footage</i>
<i>showing the workers</i>

155
00:06:00.061 --> 00:06:03.898
<i>on your property actually</i>
<i>repairing the gate in question?</i>

156
00:06:03.998 --> 00:06:05.398
<i>I'm gonna go with A.I.. Jim.</i>

157
00:06:05.498 --> 00:06:08.769
Is that a toenail?

158
00:06:08.836 --> 00:06:10.538
-It's a ghost thing.
<i>-NEWSCASTER: And what</i>
<i>about speculation...</i>

159
00:06:10.638 --> 00:06:12.306
-What?
<i>-...you used</i>
<i>city workers to build</i>

160
00:06:12.405 --> 00:06:14.575
<i>a Playboy-style grotto</i>
<i>on your private property?</i>

161
00:06:14.675 --> 00:06:17.612
<i>What about speculation</i>
<i>you were doing tequila shots</i>

162
00:06:17.712 --> 00:06:20.081
<i>in that grotto with</i>
<i>the Channel Five weather woman</i>

163
00:06:20.181 --> 00:06:21.816
<i>at my Fourth of July party?</i>

164
00:06:21.916 --> 00:06:24.051
<i>(chuckles nervously):</i>
<i>And that is all from City Hall.</i>

165
00:06:24.151 --> 00:06:26.621
<i>Yeah. I thought so. punk.</i>

166
00:06:26.721 --> 00:06:29.557
-Huh. That doesn't seem good.
-Mm. nope.

167
00:06:29.657 --> 00:06:32.260
But these things
usually blow over. right?

168
00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:35.963
Well. that's it.
I'm out as mayor.

169
00:06:36.063 --> 00:06:37.798
Oh. my God. I'm so sorry.

170
00:06:37.899 --> 00:06:40.234
No. no. it's good news
'cause I can roll up my sleeves.

171
00:06:40.334 --> 00:06:41.636
really dig in here.

172
00:06:41.736 --> 00:06:45.139
I'm all Woodstone
all the time now. baby.

173
00:06:45.239 --> 00:06:46.841
That not good.

174
00:06:46.941 --> 00:06:49.510
-Oh-oh. well. great.
-Idea:

175
00:06:49.610 --> 00:06:51.746
replace the pavers
in the front walkway.

176
00:06:51.846 --> 00:06:54.849
Also. change the wallpaper
in the entryway.

177
00:06:54.949 --> 00:06:57.118
Ugh. this is gonna be
most inconvenient.

178
00:06:57.218 --> 00:07:00.187
And have the staff
start dressing less frumpy.

179
00:07:00.288 --> 00:07:03.190
Eh. On the other hand. some
new ideas could be refreshing.

180
00:07:09.196 --> 00:07:10.831
It's not a misuse
of public resources

181
00:07:10.932 --> 00:07:12.700
to have city workers
fixing my gate.

182
00:07:12.800 --> 00:07:14.702
If I don't feel secure
on my property.

183
00:07:14.802 --> 00:07:17.470
I can't sleep. I mayor poorly.

184
00:07:17.571 --> 00:07:20.708
Thor like that. Mayor as verb.

185
00:07:20.808 --> 00:07:22.977
How do you know about verbs?

186
00:07:23.077 --> 00:07:24.879
But that's in the past.
Let's talk about the future.

187
00:07:24.979 --> 00:07:27.715
I've been doing an assessment
of the restaurant

188
00:07:27.815 --> 00:07:29.317
and the B and B.

189
00:07:29.417 --> 00:07:31.085
With regard to occupancy.

190
00:07:31.185 --> 00:07:34.555
it seems like half the rooms
are perpetually blocked off.

191
00:07:34.655 --> 00:07:37.858
-Yes. those are our bedrooms.
-THORFINN: You want guests

192
00:07:37.959 --> 00:07:40.394
rolling through ghosts
in middle of night? (laughs)

193
00:07:40.493 --> 00:07:41.896
Don't think so.

194
00:07:41.996 --> 00:07:43.397
On the website.
I mean. it seems like...

195
00:07:43.496 --> 00:07:45.066
(scoffs)
can't even book 'em.

196
00:07:45.166 --> 00:07:46.968
We prefer to create a scarcity.

197
00:07:47.068 --> 00:07:48.569
That's sort of
a business strategy.

198
00:07:48.669 --> 00:07:50.738
It's like De Beers
with the diamonds.

199
00:07:50.838 --> 00:07:52.974
(Chicago accent):
Da Beers. (laughs)

200
00:07:53.074 --> 00:07:55.076
(normal voice):
<i>SNL.</i> Ditka.

201
00:07:55.176 --> 00:07:57.411
It's a classic. Nailed it.

202
00:07:57.511 --> 00:07:59.680
Okay. Uh... Let me drill down.
get a little more practical.

203
00:07:59.780 --> 00:08:02.416
Jay. you mentioned
the spring menu earlier.

204
00:08:02.516 --> 00:08:06.220
Don't worry. I'm on it. I know
that's below your pay grade.

205
00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:07.421
Perhaps in
a pre-Gate-gate world.

206
00:08:07.521 --> 00:08:09.190
Now I got nothing but time.

207
00:08:09.290 --> 00:08:11.892
Maybe you could prepare
a sampling of the new dishes.

208
00:08:11.993 --> 00:08:13.561
I could critique 'em.

209
00:08:13.661 --> 00:08:16.330
Let's see. What other
action items do I have here?

210
00:08:16.430 --> 00:08:19.266
Jay loving this about as much
as Thor love clutter.

211
00:08:19.367 --> 00:08:20.868
Which not very much.

212
00:08:20.968 --> 00:08:23.537
Thor famously hate clutter.

213
00:08:23.637 --> 00:08:24.939
ISAAC:
Samantha. if I may.

214
00:08:25.039 --> 00:08:26.607
we're dealing
with a political animal.

215
00:08:26.707 --> 00:08:28.776
If you wish
to neutralize Mayor Tad.

216
00:08:28.876 --> 00:08:31.812
might I suggest appealing
to his massive ego.

217
00:08:33.114 --> 00:08:34.115
Tad.
(chuckles)

218
00:08:34.215 --> 00:08:36.117
As much as we love

219
00:08:36.217 --> 00:08:38.386
this feedback.
I can't help but feel like

220
00:08:38.486 --> 00:08:40.287
a great businessman like you

221
00:08:40.388 --> 00:08:41.889
shouldn't be wasting his energy

222
00:08:41.989 --> 00:08:45.659
on occupancy rates
and menu items.

223
00:08:47.294 --> 00:08:49.296
-Go on.
-JAY: Sam's right.

224
00:08:49.397 --> 00:08:51.766
Spring menu? (scoffs)
Small ball. man.

225
00:08:51.866 --> 00:08:54.602
You are a visionary.
You're a world builder.

226
00:08:54.702 --> 00:08:56.804
Oh. Oh. maybe
this-this whole scandal

227
00:08:56.904 --> 00:08:59.540
is actually an opportunity
for you to strike out

228
00:08:59.640 --> 00:09:02.511
in a bold new direction.

229
00:09:02.576 --> 00:09:04.945
You're right.
Improving this small business

230
00:09:05.046 --> 00:09:07.982
at the margins. that's-that's
not worthy of my time.

231
00:09:08.082 --> 00:09:12.353
Exactly. You need to write the
next chapter in the book of Tad.

232
00:09:12.453 --> 00:09:15.489
Yes. I need to look
at the whole board.

233
00:09:15.589 --> 00:09:17.992
This is my time
in the wilderness.

234
00:09:18.092 --> 00:09:21.162
and I shall emerge renewed.

235
00:09:21.262 --> 00:09:22.563
I just have one piece of advice

236
00:09:22.663 --> 00:09:23.764
if you're going
